# Section background color (required for new sections)

When creating or editing `sections/*.liquid`, add a **section background color** setting for the **outer/main section**, not inner cards, banners, or content boxes.

## Schema

Group under header `Section style`:

```json
{
  "type": "color",
  "id": "background_color",
  "label": "Section background color",
  "info": "Applies to the outer section only, not inner cards or banners."
}
```

Use a sensible `default` when the design calls for one (e.g. `#F8F8F8`). Empty = no override.

Inner surfaces use **separate** settings, e.g. `card_background_color`, `banner_background_color`.

## Markup & CSS

Apply to the **Shopify section wrapper** or root `<section>` — never to `.page-width`, cards, or nested wrappers.

**Preferred (scoped style block):**

```liquid
{%- if section.settings.background_color != blank -%}
  #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} {
    background-color: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
  }
{%- endif -%}
```

**Alternative (inline on root element):**

```liquid
<section
  class="my-section section-spacing"
  {% if section.settings.background_color != blank %}
    style="background-color: {{ section.settings.background_color }};"
  {% endif %}
>
```

## Do not

- Put `background_color` on inner cards, banners, or `.page-width` when it is meant to be the section backdrop
- Reuse `background_color` for both outer section and inner card — use distinct setting IDs
- Skip the setting when the section has a visible outer background area
